1. Serializer (reuse existing one) — menu/serializers.py
We already have this from your earlier tasks, but making sure it’s ready:

from rest_framework import serializers
from .models import MenuItem

class MenuItemSerializer(serializers.ModelSerializer):
    class Meta:
        model = MenuItem
        fields = ["id", "name", "description", "price", "available", "category"]

2. Create a ViewSet with search — menu/views.py
We’ll use DRF filters (SearchFilter) to enable searching by name.

from rest_framework import viewsets, filters, permissions
from .models import MenuItem
from .serializers import MenuItemSerializer

class MenuItemSearchViewSet(viewsets.ReadOnlyModelViewSet):
    """
    API endpoint to search menu items by name.
    """
    queryset = MenuItem.objects.all()
    serializer_class = MenuItemSerializer
    permission_classes = [permissions.AllowAny]  # anyone can search

    # Enable DRF's built-in search functionality
    filter_backends = [filters.SearchFilter]
    search_fields = ["name"]  # case-insensitive by default

3. Add pagination (optional but recommended) — settings.py
In your project settings:

REST_FRAMEWORK = {
    "DEFAULT_PAGINATION_CLASS": "rest_framework.pagination.PageNumberPagination",
    "PAGE_SIZE": 10,  # adjust page size as needed
}

4. Add URL routing — menu/urls.py
We’ll register this search endpoint:

from django.urls import path, include
from rest_framework.routers import DefaultRouter
from .views import MenuItemSearchViewSet

router = DefaultRouter()
router.register(r'search', MenuItemSearchViewSet, basename='menuitem-search')

urlpatterns = [
    path('', include(router.urls)),
]

5. Example Requests
Search by keyword
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/menu/search/?search=burger

